---
import LegalDocument from '~/components/LegalDocument.astro';
import { company, termsPageMeta } from '~/data/legal';

const updated = '20 May 2026';
const lead = `These terms apply to quotes and painting work arranged with us, and to general use of this website. Last updated: ${updated}.`;
---
<LegalDocument
  title={termsPageMeta.title}
  description={termsPageMeta.description}
  heading="Terms and conditions"
  lead={lead}
>
  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">About us</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are issued by <strong>{company.legalName}</strong> (company number{' '}
    <strong>{company.companyNumber}</strong>), trading as {company.tradingName}.
  </p>
  <p>
    Registered office: {company.registeredAddress}.<br />
    Email: <a href={`mailto:${company.email}`}>{company.email}</a><br />
    Phone: <a href={`tel:${company.phone.tel}`}>{company.phone.display}</a> · Freephone:{' '}
    <a href={`tel:${company.freephone.tel}`}>{company.freephone.display}</a>
  </p>
  <p>
    By using this website, submitting a quote request, or agreeing to proceed with work, you
    accept these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the site or our services.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Our services</h2>
  <p>
    We provide <strong>painting and decorating</strong> for commercial, industrial and domestic
    customers, mainly across Leicestershire. Unless agreed separately in writing:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not carry out plastering as a standalone trade</li>
    <li>We do not hang wallpaper</li>
    <li>Light filling and preparation of sound surfaces is included only as part of agreed painting work</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Scope, materials, access and any exclusions will be set out in your written quote or contract
    before work starts.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Quotes and estimates</h2>
  <p>
    Website descriptions and telephone discussions are for general information only. A binding
    price is given in our <strong>written quote</strong> after we have assessed the job (usually
    following a site visit or, for smaller domestic work, sufficient detail from you).
  </p>
  <p>
    Quotes are valid for the period stated on them. If circumstances change (for example hidden
    damage, additional areas, or client-specified changes), we will discuss revised pricing before
    continuing.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Booking work, deposits and payment</h2>
  <p>
    Dates, deposits, stage payments and final balances are confirmed in your quote or job
    confirmation. Deposits may be required to secure materials and diary space; if so, the amount
    and refund position will be stated in writing.
  </p>
  <p>
    Payment terms (due dates and methods) are as agreed on your quote. We may pause or stop work
    if agreed payments are not received, after reasonable notice.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Access, preparation and site conditions</h2>
  <p>You agree to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide safe access to the areas to be painted at agreed times</li>
    <li>Clear or protect belongings as discussed before we start, unless we have agreed to move items</li>
    <li>Tell us about hazards, asbestos, fragile surfaces, occupied areas, or restrictions (for example school hours, factory production, or live retail trading)</li>
    <li>Ensure utilities and ventilation are available where needed for the work specified</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We may request RAMS (risk assessments and method statements) on commercial or industrial sites
    and will follow reasonable site rules and induction requirements.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Delays and cancellation</h2>
  <p>
    We will use reasonable efforts to meet agreed start and finish dates. Delays caused by weather,
    supplier issues, illness, or circumstances outside our control may require rescheduling; we
    will keep you informed.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you need to cancel or postpone, please tell us as soon as possible. Cancellation charges may
    apply if we have incurred cost for materials, labour allocation or third-party bookings; any
    such charges will be explained in your quote or confirmation.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Quality, defects and complaints</h2>
  <p>
    We aim to complete work to a professional standard using appropriate preparation and trade
    paints. If you believe there is a defect in our workmanship, notify us in writing within a
    reasonable time (typically within 14 days of completion for visible interior work, or as stated
    on your quote) with enough detail for us to inspect.
  </p>
  <p>
    We will remedy genuine defects attributable to our work at no extra charge, provided you have
    allowed access for inspection and any remedy. This does not cover normal wear and tear, damage
    after handover, or issues caused by other trades, moisture, or unsuitable surfaces not disclosed
    to us.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Liability</h2>
  <p>
    We hold appropriate insurance for our business activities. Nothing in these terms excludes or
    limits liability for death or personal injury caused by negligence, fraud, or any other
    liability that cannot be limited under English law.
  </p>
  <p>
    Subject to that, our total liability for any claim arising from a specific job is limited to
    the amount paid to us for that job, except where a different limit is required by law or agreed
    in writing for a particular contract.
  </p>
  <p>
    We are not responsible for indirect or consequential loss (such as loss of profit or business
    interruption) except where required by law.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Website use</h2>
  <p>
    Content on this site (text, images, branding) is owned by or licensed to us. You may view pages
    for personal or business enquiry purposes. You must not copy, scrape or misuse the site in a
    way that could harm our systems or reputation.
  </p>
  <p>
    By submitting the quote form you confirm the information is accurate and that you agree to our{' '}
    <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Governing law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by the laws of <strong>England and Wales</strong>. Disputes are
    subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales, without prejudice
    to your statutory rights as a consumer if you qualify for them.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms from time to time. The version on this page applies from the date
    shown above. Work already agreed under a written quote will normally continue on the terms
    that applied when that quote was accepted.
  </p>

  <h2 class="legal-page__h2">Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms: <a href={`mailto:${company.email}`}>{company.email}</a> or{' '}
    <a href="/contact/">request a quote online</a>.
  </p>
</LegalDocument>
